                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Citadel is a very active neighbourhood, and it is not unusual to see locals taking walks and using the walking trails. The Crowfoot Arena (home of the Crowfoot Hockey Association), Crowfoot YMCA, and Crowfoot Library are all just a few minutes away if you prefer to stay close to home. </p>
                    <p>Couples and families may enjoy weekend vacations and day outings since Citadel is close to Stoney Trail, which provides easy access to the Rockies via the Trans-Canada Highway. </p>
                    <p>Canada Olympic Park, about 15 minutes away, is another alternative that is a little nearer to the community. It's a terrific site for beginning snowboarders and skiers to obtain training, as well as experienced sports enthusiasts to get practise runs. Summer events and activities are also available at Canada Olympic Park!</p>
                    <p>Some other amenities you can enjoy around Citadel include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 30px;">Shopping at Beacon Hill shopping district and Market Mall. </li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 30px;">Shopping at Crowfoot crossing, which is home to all kinds of shops and services, including groceries, banking, medical, cafés, restaurants, and much more. </li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 30px;">Movie enthusiasts can see the latest showings at Crowfoot Cineplex Odeon.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 30px;">The Hamptons Golf Course lies on the eastern and northern border of Citadel.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 30px;">Enjoy fitness activities at the YMCA, which boasts a gym, pool, an indoor running track, and more.</li>
                    </ul>
