        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>The neighbourhood of Citadel was developed in 1993 and offers a charming area to first-time homeowners as well as retirees.</p>
            <p>Citadel had a population of 10,197 people living in 3,479 homes in the 2012 municipal census, up 0.3% from its 2011 demographic of 10,171. In 2012, it had a total population of 3,780/km2 (9,780/sq. mi) on a land surface of 2.7 km2 (1.0 sq. mi). </p>
            <p>In 2000, the median household income in this neighbourhood was $80,085 and 7.7% of the inhabitants were considered low-income.</p>
            <p>English, Arabic, French, Mandarin, Persian, and Russian are the most prevalent languages spoken by locals.</p>
            <p>The community's median age is 37.9 years, while the median age for the rest of Calgary is 37.4 years. Charleswood has an average of 3 persons per family and a near-equal gender ratio of 50% female and male residents. Only 7% of the residents of Charleswood are above the age of 65, compared to 10% for the rest of Calgary. </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Approximately 90% of the houses in Citadel are owned by homeowners, with the other 10% occupied by tenants. Around 80% of the properties in this neighbourhood are single-family detached homes, with townhouses accounting for the majority of the remaining residential properties. The majority of the houses in this area were built during the city’s housing boom in the 1990s. This neighbourhood also offers a diverse range of housing sizes. </p>
            <p>First-time buyers and retirees wishing to settle down have traditionally sought out the neighbourhood.</p>
